different volunteers and things

00:04:13.650 --> 00:04:14.160
like that.

00:04:14.160 --> 00:04:18.089
But we had this dream of
having an automated system that

00:04:18.089 --> 00:04:21.390
would connect excess food
to homeless shelters,

00:04:21.390 --> 00:04:25.170
and have volunteers be the
solution because during college

00:04:25.170 --> 00:04:27.900
years, we had the time
to do a bunch of research

00:04:27.900 --> 00:04:30.980
and figure out that
solutions to food rescue,

00:04:30.980 --> 00:04:36.090
in terms of food rescue, existed
and had really great impact

00:04:36.090 --> 00:04:39.240
in terms of great work of
City Harvest and Food Bank

00:04:39.240 --> 00:04:40.780
and things like that.

00:04:40.780 --> 00:04:45.990
But there was a little bit of
a gap of how much food there

00:04:45.990 --> 00:04:48.330
was out there versus
what they could pick up.

00:04:48.330 --> 00:04:51.840
And so we wanted to basically
tackle that specific gap

00:04:51.840 --> 00:04:54.000
and operate in that
niche with the model

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.760
that we kind of learned and
perfected during the college

00:04:56.760 --> 00:04:57.580
years.

00:04:57.580 --> 00:05:00.360
And so we took all
that kind of together

00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:03.570
and then entered into
a venture competition,

00:05:03.570 --> 00:05:05.410
ended up winning
some seed money,

00:05:05.410 --> 00:05:09.150
and pretty much launched it
from there and kept on going.

00:05:09.150 --> 00:05:10.149
